    "assignee": null,
    "body": "If we already have the selectedProfile in hand, we don't need to talk to Yggdrasil.  When creating a client now, we always refresh the auth token to get the selected profile, causing the access token to be rotated. Passing the session information allows the user to stop the token from being rotated, so it can continue to be used.",
    "closed_at": "2015-10-08T00:53:06Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "So #262 fixed the problem that we always rotate the accessTokens. We now validate the existing tokens first, and only rotate if necessary. Removing yggdrasil entirely is outside the scope of createClient. If you need to do that, you can either use the raw Client class, or, when the modularization work ( #210 ) is done, it'll be possible to simply remove a module to bypass that.\r\n\r\nI'm keeping this open as a reminder.",
            "created_at": "2015-10-01T23:38:51Z",
